Possible solution


We should only excluded a node if no ACK and/or NACK has been received.


If there are collisions, the other node is not crashed in all cases:  maybe it can answer later or the network was oveloaded.


For now, exclusion is computed at service level. Maybe it should be done at node level ?


This routine (or an equivalent) should be add to luos in a relevant level (luos_loop ? ...?)
